paint.shared.objects

Class Track

  • java.lang.Object
    • paint.shared.objects.Track

  • public class Track
extends Object
    The Track class represents the properties and attributes of a trajectory or path recorded during an experiment. It contains various analytical properties such as displacement, speed, and diffusion coefficients as well as associated metadata like experiment and recording details.

    This class provides the necessary getters and setters for accessing and modifying its fields.

             double diffusionCoefficient,
             double diffusionCoefficientExt,
             double totalDistance,
             double confinementRatio,
             int squareNumber,
             int labelNumber)
        Full constructor to initialize all fields of a Track.
        Parameters:
        uniqueKey - unique identifier for the track
        experimentName - name of the experiment the track belongs to
        recordingName - name of the recording the track belongs to
        trackId - numerical track identifier
        numberOfSpots - number of spots in the track
        numberOfGaps - number of gaps in the track
        longestGap - longest gap between spots
        trackDuration - total duration of the track
        trackXLocation - average X location
        trackYLocation - average Y location
        trackDisplacement - net displacement from start to end
        trackMaxSpeed - maximum speed recorded
        trackMedianSpeed - median speed recorded
        diffusionCoefficient - diffusion coefficient
        diffusionCoefficientExt - extended diffusion coefficient
        totalDistance - total distance traveled
        confinementRatio - ratio of displacement to total distance
        squareNumber - square index containing this track
        labelNumber - label index used for annotation
